## WHAT WE ARE BUILDING

A platform where professors upload course materials (PDFs, slides, notes)
and students interact with an AI teaching assistant ("Mini Professor") that
answers questions strictly grounded in those uploaded materials using RAG
(Retrieval-Augmented Generation).

---

## PROJECT STRUCTURE

```
mini-professor/
├── frontend/          # Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind
├── backend/           # FastAPI (Python) — all AI logic lives here
├── .cursorrules       # This file
└── README.md
```

---

## TECH STACK — NEVER DEVIATE FROM THIS

### Frontend
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router (NOT pages router)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- State: Zustand for global state, React Query (TanStack) for server state
- HTTP: axios for API calls
- Streaming: EventSource / SSE for streaming LLM responses
- NO Redux, NO class components, NO CSS modules

### Backend (AI Engine)
- Framework: FastAPI (Python 3.10+)
- AI Orchestration: LangChain + LangGraph
- Document Parsing: LlamaIndex (for PDF/PPTX/DOCX ingestion)
- Embeddings: OpenAI text-embedding-3-small
- LLM: GPT-4o for answers, GPT-4o-mini for classification
- Vector DB: Qdrant (running locally via Docker)
- Reranking: Cohere Rerank API
- Observability: LangSmith
- Package manager: pip with requirements.txt

### Database
- PostgreSQL via SQLAlchemy (async) — users, courses, documents metadata
- Qdrant — vector embeddings

### Infrastructure (local dev → demo)
- Docker Compose for Qdrant + PostgreSQL locally
- Environment variables via .env files (never hardcode keys)

---

## AI ARCHITECTURE — CORE RAG PIPELINE

```
PDF Upload → S3/Local Storage
     ↓
LlamaIndex Parser (extracts text + metadata)
     ↓
Hierarchical Chunking (2048 → 512 → 128 tokens)
     ↓
OpenAI Embeddings (text-embedding-3-small)
     ↓
Qdrant Vector Store (with metadata filters: course_id, professor_id)
     ↓
[At query time]
User Question → HyDE Query Expansion → Hybrid Retrieval (Dense + BM25)
     ↓
Cohere Reranker (top 20 → top 5)
     ↓
GPT-4o with grounded prompt + citation injection
     ↓
Streaming response to frontend
```

---

## CODING RULES — ALWAYS FOLLOW

### General
- Always use async/await — never blocking calls in FastAPI
- All API routes return consistent JSON: `{ success: bool, data: any, error: str | null }`
- Every function must have a docstring explaining what it does
- Use Pydantic models for ALL request/response schemas in FastAPI
- Use TypeScript interfaces for ALL API response types in frontend
- Never hardcode API keys — always use os.getenv() in Python, process.env in JS

### Python / FastAPI
- Use `async def` for all route handlers
- SQLAlchemy models go in `backend/models/`
- Pydantic schemas go in `backend/schemas/`
- AI pipeline logic goes in `backend/services/`
- API routes go in `backend/routers/`
- Config/settings go in `backend/core/config.py` using pydantic-settings
- Always handle exceptions with try/except and return proper HTTP error codes

### Next.js / TypeScript
- All pages go in `frontend/app/` (App Router structure)
- Reusable components go in `frontend/components/`
- API calls go in `frontend/lib/api.ts`
- Types go in `frontend/types/`
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed (mark with 'use client')
- Always handle loading and error states in UI

### RAG / AI Code
- All LangChain/LLM code goes in `backend/services/rag/`
- Prompts go in `backend/services/rag/prompts.py` as named constants
- Never put raw prompt strings inside route handlers
- Always filter Qdrant queries by course_id — never allow cross-course retrieval
- Every LLM call must be traced in LangSmith
- Citations must always be included in responses

---

## FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS

- Python files: snake_case (e.g., `rag_service.py`)
- TypeScript files: camelCase for utils, PascalCase for components (e.g., `ChatWindow.tsx`)
- Environment files: `.env.local` (frontend), `.env` (backend)

---

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES REQUIRED

### backend/.env
```
OPENAI_API_KEY=
COHERE_API_KEY=
LANGCHAIN_API_KEY=        # LangSmith
LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2=true
LANGCHAIN_PROJECT=mini-professor
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:password@localhost:5432/miniprofessor
QDRANT_URL=http://localhost:6333
QDRANT_API_KEY=           # leave empty for local
UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
```

### frontend/.env.local
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

